ft class=m><span class=title>   Permafrost</span><hr size=1> Ok...not exactly a full on raid so I decided to just put it here. As you know, I need Zaharn's coronet for my final headband so I can start working on the robe of the lost circle quest (which leads tot he robe of the whistling fist, which leads to the monk epic). I'm not good at researching or planning out things, so here's the gist of it. <br>
<br>
Permafrost is located north (I think) of Everfrost (I think that's the name of the zone). The way in is through a back door into ice giant territory or through the front through 4 ice giant spawn points (which are usually camped anyway). It takes one really solid group of lvl 30's to 40's or two smaller groups (at least from what I experienced). I was grouping with two lvl 30 warriors with one lvl 42 wizard and a lvl 30 druid. There was someone else, but I don't remember. As you go in, we'll go past the &quot;flag room&quot; with a big flag in the middle to some gates (that's as far as I've gone). The &quot;King's room&quot; is where I want to head into since that's where the coronet is. Up to the gate, everything was green. From there, we just pulled goblins until we made a few dents into the room. Unfortunatly, we had to evac because there was either a wandering ice giant or someone couldn't control their pull. Either way, it's something to be careful about. <br>
<br>
Some other noticeable stuff:<br>
1) the Permafrost snowball can be found here from the goblin wizards for the totemic greaves quest from Lake Rathetear<br>
AC: +12 Cha: +5 Fire Resist: +5  <br>
Weight: 4.2 <br>
Classes: Shaman  <br>
Races: Ogre Troll Barbarian Vah Shir  <br>
<br>
2) The Icy greaves from the Elite Goblin Guards for the Lambent Greaves quest for Bards.<br>
<br>
3)Gee Golly I'm tired.<br>
<br>
4) The Frost Goblin Skin for the Robe of the Elements Quest for Mages<br>
<br>
5) The Heart of Frost for some Wizzy quest.<br>
<br>
6) There's also some scales off of Vox needed for the Bard epic, but I don't think we want to tackle that...<br>
<br>
7) Last but not least, a Quivering Quijibo for all your monkey needs.<br>
<br>
Think I've wasted enough space...'nuff said.<br>
<br>
Kage no Tora<br>
